metadata.name: Pages From A Redacted Document #43
metadata.description:
In a time of mistrust, fear and corruption this work looks to reflect how transparency and accountability are removed from those with responsibility with a simple black line.

An abstract representation of the murky world that lurks behind the corridors of power. Kept there hidden and away from the masses.  We demand more.

A representation of documents printed and hand written, that are augmented with highlighters and blocking out pens.

press 'S' to download the hi-res version, which will show the full detail.

metadata.name: Cradle #192
metadata.description:
Billions of years old, ancient remains decay across our Solar System. Mere transient visitors to our star, their ephemeral presence on our worlds is embodied in their creations. In the shadow of their megalithic constructions, we wonder what they might have brought to us.

They brought life.

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #378
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Orchard #305
metadata.description:
A natural media rendering of a fruit tree during one of the four seasons. Sometimes, you'll catch it at night - with lights strung on the tree!

The amount of color in spring and fall, snow in winter, fruit on and off the tree will all vary. There are four spring bloom palettes, four trunk colors, and seven types of fruit. 

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1000x1000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

To render a variation at a new size, open live view and append '?size=#' to the end of the URL. The new size may be from 100 to 3,000. This version will not be a 1:1 match to your edition but will have all of the same features.

metadata.name: 70s Tapestry #2
metadata.description:
70s Tapestry is a tribute to the fine art work of embroiderers, and the 70s design.

Variations include :

- 10 Color Palettes
- Dark or Light background
- A reversed color mode
- 1 or 2 palettes used
- 4 types of framing, including a randomized one
- 3 types of embroidery tile type distribution
- and some special rare traits
